WEBVTT

00:03.307 --> 00:05.179
Mr. Occipinti: Come in, people!
Come on in! Find a seat.

00:05.222 --> 00:06.397
This is gonna be awesome.

00:06.441 --> 00:08.399
I can't wait to get
behind that wheel.

00:08.443 --> 00:10.271
Hang a Louie on the I-4.

00:10.314 --> 00:13.056
Dude, I've already been driving
all summer with my parents.

00:13.100 --> 00:15.711
Me too. Long trips.

00:15.754 --> 00:17.887
I drive, my mom
stares out the window,

00:17.930 --> 00:19.932
and we both think
of what it would've been like

00:19.976 --> 00:21.195
if we never
got out of Memphis.

00:21.238 --> 00:22.718
I didn't know everyone
was driving.

00:22.761 --> 00:24.676
Don't worry, Eddie.
I'm with you.

00:24.720 --> 00:26.461
My sisters refuse
to let me drive.

00:26.504 --> 00:28.419
They say I get
too many leg spasms.

00:28.463 --> 00:30.291
Eddie, you have calm legs.
Why haven't you driven?

00:30.334 --> 00:31.727
Have you met my parents?

00:31.770 --> 00:32.902
Are you
gonna have trouble

00:32.945 --> 00:34.208
getting them to sign
the permission slip?

00:34.251 --> 00:35.165
[ Thumps ]

00:36.775 --> 00:39.561
Mnh. No. I have
an airtight plan.

00:39.604 --> 00:40.997
I'm going to hit up
my dad

00:41.041 --> 00:43.173
during a monthly father-son trip
to the mustard shop.

00:43.217 --> 00:45.480
Fancy mustard always
puts him in a good mood.

00:45.523 --> 00:47.134
[ Horn honks
"Shave and a Haircut" ]

00:47.177 --> 00:50.224
♪♪

00:50.267 --> 00:52.313
What's up, suckers?

00:52.356 --> 00:53.444
Pretty nice day.

00:53.488 --> 00:55.359
Figured I'd ride my hog.

00:55.403 --> 00:57.318
How did you get
your driver's license?

00:57.361 --> 00:59.015
I'm older than you guys.

00:59.059 --> 01:02.323
I stayed back in second grade.
On purpose.

01:02.366 --> 01:03.585
Liked the upcoming talent
better.

01:03.628 --> 01:05.326
What's it like?
Driving?

01:05.369 --> 01:08.329
On your own?
No one screaming at your leg?

01:08.372 --> 01:10.331
It's like...flying

01:10.374 --> 01:12.246
while sitting down.

01:12.289 --> 01:14.683
♪♪

01:14.726 --> 01:18.339
Damn!
I gotta get my license.

01:18.382 --> 01:20.689
--Captions by VITAC--

01:20.732 --> 01:22.256
♪ Fresh off the boat

01:22.299 --> 01:23.779
♪ I'm gettin' mine
everywhere I go ♪

01:23.822 --> 01:25.955
♪ If you don't know, homey,
now you know ♪

01:25.998 --> 01:27.391
♪ Fresh off the boat

01:27.435 --> 01:29.611
♪ Homey, you don't know
where I come from ♪

01:29.654 --> 01:31.047
♪ But I know where I'm goin'

01:31.091 --> 01:33.745
♪ I'm fresh off the boat

01:33.789 --> 01:35.312
♪♪

01:35.356 --> 01:37.401
Permission slip
for Driver's Ed.

01:37.445 --> 01:39.186
My airtight plan.
How?

01:39.229 --> 01:42.058
Your teachers may take
the summers off from
you, but not from me.

01:42.102 --> 01:43.277
I meet with them in July

01:43.320 --> 01:45.148
and go over the upcoming
lesson plan.

01:45.192 --> 01:46.541
Even I didn't know
she did that.

01:46.584 --> 01:48.282
Look, I need this.
I'll do anything.

01:48.325 --> 01:49.413
I'll -- I'll cook.
I'll clean.

01:49.457 --> 01:50.936
I'll stop smelling bad --

01:50.980 --> 01:52.590
Wait. You signed it?

01:52.634 --> 01:54.201
Of course.

01:54.244 --> 01:55.941
The quicker you can drive,
the quicker

01:55.985 --> 01:57.204
I can stop being
the family taximan.

01:57.247 --> 01:59.075
Oh, my God.
Let's go right now.

01:59.119 --> 02:00.816
No way.
You learn on our car,

02:00.859 --> 02:03.079
we'll need new brakes,
new bumpers, new rods.

02:03.123 --> 02:04.733
You can learn at school.

02:04.776 --> 02:06.430
But that's months
of classroom time

02:06.474 --> 02:08.084
before we even get
in the car!

02:08.128 --> 02:09.912
I know.
I have the lesson plan.

02:11.392 --> 02:14.612
What your mom means to say is,
this is a big responsibility.

02:14.656 --> 02:16.658
No need to rush.
Enjoy the process.

02:16.701 --> 02:18.834
This is the milestone
of young adulthood.

02:18.877 --> 02:20.227
I can think
of a better one.

02:22.011 --> 02:24.448
In Taiwan, I was driving a bus
when I was 11.

02:24.492 --> 02:27.408
[ Scoffs ] I didn't have
the luxury to take my time.

02:27.451 --> 02:28.757
I had to learn on the fly...

02:28.800 --> 02:31.325
with the constant fear
of delivering myself

02:31.368 --> 02:34.980
and a busload of commuters
to a fiery death.

02:35.024 --> 02:37.113
I lost my thermos
on the first day.

02:37.157 --> 02:39.289
♪♪

02:43.380 --> 02:46.035
I have some vacuuming to do,
but maybe after I finish,

02:46.078 --> 02:47.210
we can continue
our Boggle match?

02:47.254 --> 02:48.690
[ Dice rattling ]

02:48.733 --> 02:50.474
Sorry. I have
a commitment later.

02:50.518 --> 02:52.476
Oh, you have
a commitment,do you?

02:52.520 --> 02:56.350
I'd love to know what's more
important than Boggle Brothers.

02:56.393 --> 02:58.395
Grandma invited me to hang out
at her new place.

02:58.439 --> 03:02.094
It's the garage.
The old tenant was a car!

03:02.138 --> 03:04.488
And in the future,
when we get invited out,

03:04.532 --> 03:06.273
can you put it on the calendar
so I know?

03:06.316 --> 03:08.797
Luckily, I keep
my Saturdays light.

03:08.840 --> 03:11.626
Actually,
Grandma only invited me.

03:11.669 --> 03:14.933
What?!
We're a package deal.

03:14.977 --> 03:16.500
Who invites butter
but not the rolls?!

03:18.415 --> 03:19.808
[ Sighs ]

03:19.851 --> 03:21.462
-I got you. I got you.
-[ Fussing ]

03:21.505 --> 03:23.246
Louis: [ Chuckles ]

03:23.290 --> 03:25.074
Someone's a little
fussy pants.

03:25.117 --> 03:27.859
[ Chuckles ] A little?
I'm allfussy pants.

03:27.903 --> 03:29.121
-[ Laughs ]
-[ Fusses ]

03:29.165 --> 03:31.298
There we go.
Okay.

03:31.341 --> 03:33.735
She just won't sleep, Lou.
Mm.

03:33.778 --> 03:36.477
I swear, Honey's serving up
coffee milk.

03:36.520 --> 03:37.260
Can I drive?!

03:37.304 --> 03:38.479
Nope.

03:38.522 --> 03:39.523
Where are you guys off to?

03:39.567 --> 03:41.699
Eddie and I are taking
our monthly excursion

03:41.743 --> 03:43.266
to The Mustard Squeeze.

03:43.310 --> 03:44.485
Oh, man, I wish I had

03:44.528 --> 03:46.182
had a dad like you.

03:46.226 --> 03:48.140
-[ Chuckles ]
-You know, one that prepares

03:48.184 --> 03:49.490
his son for the world

03:49.533 --> 03:50.404
and everything in it.

03:50.447 --> 03:51.405
I don't know about that.

03:51.448 --> 03:52.406
I'm serious, Lou.

03:52.449 --> 03:54.538
I was thrown to the wolves.

03:54.582 --> 03:55.496
No one protected me.

03:55.539 --> 03:57.062
No one taught me

03:57.106 --> 03:59.282
that there were good
and bad mustards out there.

03:59.326 --> 04:01.458
Your kid, no matter what
sandwich comes his way,

04:01.502 --> 04:03.939
is gonna know what to put
on it because of you.

04:03.982 --> 04:06.724
[ Chuckles ]
Is this still about mustard?

04:06.768 --> 04:07.725
Yeah.

04:07.769 --> 04:08.900
No.

04:08.944 --> 04:10.119
I don't know.

04:10.162 --> 04:11.163
[ Sighs ]

04:11.207 --> 04:12.948
Well, you know,
when Eddie was a baby

04:12.991 --> 04:15.559
and wouldn't sleep, I'd put him
in the car and drive him around.

04:15.603 --> 04:16.517
He'd pass right out.

04:16.560 --> 04:18.214
Just like that?
Huh?

04:20.564 --> 04:22.305
Works every time.

04:22.349 --> 04:25.874
[ Mysterious music plays ]

04:25.917 --> 04:28.572
♪♪

04:28.616 --> 04:32.228
[ All speaking Mandarin ]

04:42.630 --> 04:44.588
Why would you cover
an owl's cage at night?

04:44.632 --> 04:45.937
They're nocturnal.

04:45.981 --> 04:48.766
Hmm.

04:48.810 --> 04:51.378
I was looking for the hourglass
timer for Boggle.

04:51.421 --> 04:53.510
Hope I didn't interrupt
anything important.

04:53.554 --> 04:56.905
No. Grandma was just telling me
about how her and Yeye met.

04:56.948 --> 04:58.515
Oh. I'd love to hear
that story.

05:08.656 --> 05:10.266
I can just hold the wheel
and steer

05:10.310 --> 05:11.615
if you want to rest
your arms.

05:11.659 --> 05:12.921
I know what you're doing.

05:12.964 --> 05:14.401
You think because I'm full
of gourmet mustard

05:14.444 --> 05:16.054
and away from your mom,
I'll give in.

05:16.098 --> 05:17.229
Nice try.

05:18.448 --> 05:22.583
Oh, car trouble. I'm gonna
see if they need any help.

05:22.626 --> 05:24.411
Stay in here.

05:25.586 --> 05:27.544
Hey!
You need some help?

05:27.588 --> 05:29.024
I think
it's just overheated.

05:30.547 --> 05:31.853
Probably just your rods.

05:31.896 --> 05:33.724
[ Siren chirps ]

05:33.768 --> 05:36.379
Oh. Hmm.

05:36.423 --> 05:39.251
All right, sir, can you tell me
how you caused the accident?

05:39.295 --> 05:41.210
E-Excuse me?

05:41.253 --> 05:42.820
No, it wasn't him.
He was just --

05:42.864 --> 05:44.213
No, you don't have to
cover for him.

05:44.256 --> 05:45.432
We all know
whose fault it was.

05:45.475 --> 05:47.259
Uh...his car overheated.

05:47.303 --> 05:49.218
I pulled over to help.
There was no accident.

05:49.261 --> 05:50.654
Oh. [ Chuckles ]

05:50.698 --> 05:52.743
Well,
that's a nice surprise.

05:52.787 --> 05:55.311
Normally, it's, you know...
[ Imitates radio dispatcher ]

05:55.355 --> 05:56.878
"We got another crash
on Sycamore

05:56.921 --> 05:59.446
due to, you guessed it,
Asians. Over."

05:59.489 --> 06:02.057
Uh...what is that
supposed to mean?

06:02.100 --> 06:04.233
Oh, come on, I'm joking.

06:04.276 --> 06:07.279
You get it!
[ Laughs ]

06:07.323 --> 06:09.194
I'm not a racist.
Come on.

06:09.238 --> 06:11.414
My -- My training officer
was Korean.

06:11.458 --> 06:13.547
Marvin: Man, I wish
I had a dad like you...

06:13.590 --> 06:15.070
one that prepares your son

06:15.113 --> 06:17.551
for the world
and everything in it.

06:17.594 --> 06:19.509
No one protected me.

06:19.553 --> 06:21.206
No one taught me

06:21.250 --> 06:22.991
that there were good and bad
mustards out there.

06:23.034 --> 06:24.775
Hey, do you understand
the words

06:24.819 --> 06:26.255
that are coming out
of my mouth?!

06:26.298 --> 06:28.692
[ Chuckles ]

06:28.736 --> 06:30.302
It's "Rush Hour."

06:30.346 --> 06:32.217
[ Scoffs ] It's the best movie
of the summer,

06:32.261 --> 06:33.349
possibly of all time.

06:33.393 --> 06:34.698
I, uh, haven't seen it.

06:34.742 --> 06:36.526
How have younot seen it?

06:36.570 --> 06:38.528
You would loveit!

06:38.572 --> 06:40.661
[ Laughs ]

06:40.704 --> 06:44.665
♪♪

06:44.708 --> 06:45.927
I'm gonna teach you
to drive.

06:45.970 --> 06:47.624
You're gonna be the best damn
driver on the road.

06:47.668 --> 06:49.713
Holy...nuts.

06:49.757 --> 06:51.280
Seriously?! What happened?[ Seat belt clicks ]

06:51.323 --> 06:52.803
The officer was just
reminding me

06:52.847 --> 06:54.457
how dangerous it is
out there.

06:54.501 --> 06:56.720
And it's my job to make sure
you're prepared.

06:56.764 --> 06:58.635
This is the best
mustard trip ever!

07:02.639 --> 07:03.814
All right, hydrate,

07:03.858 --> 07:05.468
do some light stretching,
and get some sleep.

07:05.512 --> 07:06.643
Training starts tomorrow.

07:06.687 --> 07:08.863
I can't believe
I'm finally gonna drive.

07:08.906 --> 07:11.431
I'm never walking into
another Wendy's in my life.

07:12.388 --> 07:13.520
-Heeeey!
-Heeeey!

07:13.563 --> 07:15.173
No mustard talk.
It gives me a headache.

07:15.217 --> 07:16.000
-Yep.
-We know!

07:17.349 --> 07:19.830
-How you gonna convince her?
-Got an airtight plan.

07:19.874 --> 07:22.398
First, a compliment --
play to her ego.

07:22.442 --> 07:24.835
Then a philosophical question
that we can debate for hours.

07:24.879 --> 07:26.924
Once I exhaust
her argumentative powers,

07:26.968 --> 07:28.709
I'll put on the charm,
and she'll cave.

07:32.016 --> 07:33.540
[ Sighs ]

07:38.109 --> 07:39.720
You're so good
at balancing the checkbook.

07:43.724 --> 07:46.378
So...you ever think
they'll create a robot

07:46.422 --> 07:47.379
that can feel joy?

07:47.423 --> 07:49.207
No.

07:49.251 --> 07:50.600
Mmm...

07:53.429 --> 07:54.561
I love you so much.

07:54.604 --> 07:55.779
You are up to something.

07:55.823 --> 07:57.302
My airtight plan. How?!

07:57.346 --> 07:58.478
Spill it.

08:01.176 --> 08:02.743
I want to teach Eddie
to drive.

08:02.786 --> 08:04.309
He needs to be ready.
More than ready.

08:04.353 --> 08:05.876
No. We agreed.

08:05.920 --> 08:09.227
I know, but I forgot about this
bad-Asian-driver stereotype.

08:09.271 --> 08:10.402
You forgot about it?

08:10.446 --> 08:12.230
You make those jokes
all the time.

08:12.274 --> 08:13.580
I do not!

08:13.623 --> 08:14.711
What about this morning?

08:16.147 --> 08:17.758
[ Thumping ]

08:17.801 --> 08:21.805
[ Laughs ]
Asian driver coming through!

08:21.849 --> 08:23.764
It's okay, Louis.

08:23.807 --> 08:25.766
Wecan joke about it.
We are Asian.

08:25.809 --> 08:27.898
Also, I back into the trash cans
twice a week.

08:27.942 --> 08:29.552
That's because you're
a careless driver,

08:29.596 --> 08:30.597
not because you're Asian.

08:30.640 --> 08:31.728
Are we sure?

08:32.947 --> 08:34.775
I'm joking. Kind of.

08:34.818 --> 08:36.820
I thought it was just
a dumb thing, too,

08:36.864 --> 08:38.822
until I realized Eddie's
going to be facing it now.

08:38.866 --> 08:40.781
I'm sure he knows
all about it.

08:40.824 --> 08:43.131
He's 15
and he reads Angrymagazine.

08:43.174 --> 08:44.698
It's MADmagazine.

08:44.741 --> 08:45.742
And there's
a huge difference

08:45.786 --> 08:47.570
between reading clever satire
at home

08:47.614 --> 08:49.398
and being out there,
vulnerable,

08:49.441 --> 08:51.618
exposed to this nonsense.

08:51.661 --> 08:53.707
I never thought
about it that way.

08:53.750 --> 08:55.839
We stopped to help someone
on the side of the road today,

08:55.883 --> 08:57.624
and the cop just assumed
that I caused an accident.

08:57.667 --> 08:59.060
Did Eddie hear this?

08:59.103 --> 09:00.975
No, but it's only
a matter of time.

09:01.018 --> 09:03.499
If he stops too short
or leaves the blinkers on,

09:03.543 --> 09:04.848
it'll be thrown in his face,

09:04.892 --> 09:07.155
even though everyone else
drives the same way!

09:07.198 --> 09:09.766
People do stick
their finger up at me a lot.

09:09.810 --> 09:11.463
Jessica,
the stereotype's out there.

09:11.507 --> 09:12.987
We can't change that.

09:13.030 --> 09:15.467
But we can try to protect our
son from it the best we can,

09:15.511 --> 09:17.600
which means he has to be
doubly prepared, not less.

09:17.644 --> 09:20.516
Okay, you can train him.

09:20.560 --> 09:21.604
Really?

09:21.648 --> 09:23.301
Yes,
I'm gonna go tell Eddie.

09:23.345 --> 09:26.000
Louis, sometimes he can be
a little slow on the uptake,

09:26.043 --> 09:28.089
so better triple train him
to be safe.

09:28.132 --> 09:31.788
♪♪

09:31.832 --> 09:33.747
Where've you been?

09:33.790 --> 09:36.793
Went for a walk.
Fresh air.

09:36.837 --> 09:39.796
I've asked you to walk with me
and the HOA ladies

09:39.840 --> 09:42.233
every day
for four straight years.

09:42.277 --> 09:45.802
Suddenly, tonight you catch
a hot case of walking fever?

09:45.846 --> 09:47.848
I heard the moon
was really big, and I --

09:47.891 --> 09:49.806
I saw your bike parked
on the side of the garage.

09:49.850 --> 09:51.765
It always is now
that Grandma lives in there.

09:51.808 --> 09:54.115
How long have these little hangs
been going on?

09:54.158 --> 09:55.899
I don't know.
When she first moved out there,

09:55.943 --> 09:57.248
I thought she'd be lonely,

09:57.292 --> 09:59.033
so I brought her
a housewarming present --

09:59.076 --> 10:00.512
a nice fern.

10:00.556 --> 10:02.689
That's it! Of course!

10:02.732 --> 10:04.473
She hasn't invited me
out there

10:04.516 --> 10:05.996
because she's mad
I didn't get her a gift.

10:06.040 --> 10:07.476
Maybe.

10:07.519 --> 10:09.260
Now to figure out
what to get

10:09.304 --> 10:11.654
for the woman who has
everything.

10:11.698 --> 10:13.656
Did you get a pot
to go with that fern?

10:13.700 --> 10:14.657
Yeah.

10:14.701 --> 10:16.703
Ugh! Emery!

10:16.746 --> 10:18.922
All right.
Let's do this.

10:18.966 --> 10:20.315
I promise
to keep it under 75.

10:20.358 --> 10:21.795
What's that?

10:21.838 --> 10:23.579
Oh,
it's your first lesson.

10:23.623 --> 10:25.363
Whoa. Robbing a bank!

10:25.407 --> 10:27.583
I'm gonna learn how to drive
getaway style!

10:27.627 --> 10:28.889
No, it's a tire iron.

10:28.932 --> 10:30.542
You have to learn how
the machine works

10:30.586 --> 10:32.022
before you can be
expected to master it.

10:32.066 --> 10:34.503
Rotate the tires.
Change the oil, the spark plugs.

10:34.546 --> 10:35.939
Check the fluid.

10:35.983 --> 10:37.941
My friends didn't have to learn
any of this nonsense.

10:37.985 --> 10:40.074
They're already driving!
Brian has a hog!

10:40.117 --> 10:41.728
I made a deal
with your mom.

10:41.771 --> 10:43.599
If you want to use our car,

10:43.643 --> 10:45.470
you're gonna have to
learn my way.

10:45.514 --> 10:47.690
You gotta stop
making deals with Mom.

10:47.734 --> 10:49.692
She tricks you every time.

10:49.736 --> 10:50.693
Go![ Stopwatch beeps ]

10:50.737 --> 10:54.741
♪♪

10:54.784 --> 10:58.788
♪♪

10:58.832 --> 10:59.963
10:00 and 2:00.

11:00.007 --> 11:02.705
♪♪

11:02.749 --> 11:05.055
Heavy mist.

11:05.099 --> 11:06.709
Steady rain.

11:06.753 --> 11:09.756
Downpour.

11:09.799 --> 11:13.411
♪♪

11:13.455 --> 11:15.370
Brake. Accelerate.

11:15.413 --> 11:16.980
Right turn. Brake.

11:17.024 --> 11:18.721
[ Squeals]

11:18.765 --> 11:21.115
Rainbow Road!

11:21.158 --> 11:22.159
Go!

11:22.203 --> 11:26.990
♪♪

11:27.034 --> 11:27.991
10:00 and 2:00.

11:28.035 --> 11:29.079
[ Stopwatch beeps ]

11:29.123 --> 11:31.952
♪♪

11:31.995 --> 11:32.735
[ Chuckles ]

11:32.779 --> 11:35.346
I think you're ready.
Show me what you got.

11:35.390 --> 11:38.828
Okay. I checked
the tire pressure,

11:38.872 --> 11:40.787
adjusted the mirror,
released the parking brake,

11:40.830 --> 11:43.528
turned off the radio,
and buckled my seatbelt.

11:43.572 --> 11:44.747
Is that everything?

11:47.924 --> 11:49.143
Forgot to check
your blind spot.

11:49.186 --> 11:50.884
No, I did.
You just missed it.

11:50.927 --> 11:52.624
Oh, yeah, Jessica?

11:52.668 --> 11:54.670
I don't know how you didn't
smell my sunscreen.

11:56.498 --> 11:57.934
You just got in an accident

11:57.978 --> 11:59.675
because you didn't
check your blind spot.

11:59.719 --> 12:01.024
I'm parked
in my own driveway.

12:01.068 --> 12:03.026
Most accidents happen
within a mile of home.

12:03.070 --> 12:04.027
I'm at home!

12:04.071 --> 12:05.159
That's within a mile.

12:05.202 --> 12:06.595
We can try again
next weekend.

12:06.638 --> 12:07.770
Next weekend?!

12:07.814 --> 12:10.207
Forget it. I'm just
gonna wait for school.

12:10.251 --> 12:12.644
Listen, this is
a big moment in your life,

12:12.688 --> 12:14.037
and I wanted it
to be perfect.

12:14.081 --> 12:15.952
But the truth is,
there's this stereotype --

12:15.996 --> 12:17.214
Asians suck at driving?

12:17.258 --> 12:18.999
Yeah, I've heard that crap.
Who cares?

12:19.042 --> 12:19.826
You will! I know you.

12:19.869 --> 12:21.915
When you get blamed
for every little thing

12:21.958 --> 12:24.134
that goes wrong on the road
whether it's your fault or not.

12:24.178 --> 12:25.788
So, because people
are stupid,

12:25.832 --> 12:27.921
I have to do
twice as much work?

12:27.964 --> 12:29.226
I'm not saying it's fair.

12:29.270 --> 12:31.576
Eddie, you can half-ass this
if you want.

12:31.620 --> 12:32.969
Maybe add
to the stereotype.

12:33.013 --> 12:34.971
Or you can try to
rail against it...

12:35.015 --> 12:36.886
by being better.

12:36.930 --> 12:38.888
It's your choice.

12:38.932 --> 12:41.412
I hate that your "be the change"
speech always gets to me.

12:41.456 --> 12:42.457
[ Keys rattle ]

12:42.500 --> 12:45.460
[ Door motor whirring ]

12:45.503 --> 12:47.288
Like what you see?
Take a picture.

12:47.331 --> 12:48.768
It will last longer.

12:49.856 --> 12:51.335
Bearskin rug, eh?

12:53.729 --> 12:55.687
So soft.

12:55.731 --> 12:57.298
Maybe we all sit
and break it in

12:57.341 --> 12:59.779
while you finish the story
of how you met Yeye.

13:11.921 --> 13:13.488
All right,
what's the deal?

13:13.531 --> 13:15.969
I gave her a present 10 times
better than your lame-o fern,

13:16.012 --> 13:18.275
and she's still not giving me
the time of day.

13:18.319 --> 13:20.103
Maybe you're trying
too hard.

13:20.147 --> 13:22.540
I'm not buying your cheese.
Spill it!

13:22.584 --> 13:25.456
Okay, Grandma doesn't like
telling her stories to you

13:25.500 --> 13:28.068
because, well, you know
how you are.

13:28.111 --> 13:29.330
A delight?

13:29.373 --> 13:31.985
You've been known to suck
the fun out of things.

13:32.028 --> 13:34.944
Or as Grandma says,
you're a stick-in-the-mud.

13:34.988 --> 13:36.337
[ Gasps ]

13:36.380 --> 13:38.078
A stick-in-the-mud?!

13:38.121 --> 13:38.905
I'll have you know

13:38.948 --> 13:41.168
a beaver would call that
the start to a house!

13:43.039 --> 13:44.867
I got to honk the horn
for the first time.

13:44.911 --> 13:47.000
It felt so good!

13:47.043 --> 13:48.523
Yeah, they say you
never forget your first.

13:48.566 --> 13:50.351
I sure didn't.

13:50.394 --> 13:52.048
Hooonnnnnk!

13:52.092 --> 13:54.964
My dad says the most effective
honk is good defensive driving.

13:56.574 --> 13:58.533
Why are you wearing those gloves
if you can't drive?

13:58.576 --> 14:01.057
My sisters realized I can be
their designated driver.

14:01.101 --> 14:03.059
Now they let me drive
all the time.

14:03.103 --> 14:04.974
Trish met a guy from Tampa
in a bar,

14:05.018 --> 14:06.889
and I cruised them
all the way home

14:06.933 --> 14:08.543
while they got busy
in the back seat.

14:08.586 --> 14:10.501
What?!
You'redriving now?!

14:10.545 --> 14:12.590
Welcome to Honktown.

14:12.634 --> 14:17.987
♪♪

14:24.124 --> 14:25.995
Yeah, it's a good batch.

14:26.039 --> 14:27.083
[ Engine revs ]

14:27.127 --> 14:28.171
Oh, Marvin...

14:34.090 --> 14:36.179
I wonder if he's taking Maria
for a drive

14:36.223 --> 14:37.659
to get her to sleep.

14:40.662 --> 14:42.055
What the hell?!

14:42.098 --> 14:46.146
♪♪

14:46.189 --> 14:47.103
Eddie's on the lam!
Where are my keys?

14:47.147 --> 14:48.148
[ Tires screech ]

14:48.191 --> 14:49.801
[ Crashing ]

14:53.805 --> 14:55.633
-Eddie!
-Everyone's okay, Lou.

14:55.677 --> 14:58.288
I was too tired to drive,
so Eddie was helping me out.

14:58.332 --> 14:59.768
No one got hurt.

14:59.811 --> 15:01.944
Oh, really?
Bianca looks okay to you?

15:01.988 --> 15:03.076
Eddie, what did you do?

15:03.119 --> 15:05.556
Me? Why do you think
I caused this?

15:05.600 --> 15:07.210
Because
you're inexperienced.

15:07.254 --> 15:10.083
Brian just started driving, too.
Why don't you blame him?

15:10.126 --> 15:11.998
Is it 'cause I'm Asian?

15:12.041 --> 15:14.087
I don't see faces.
I see cars.

15:14.130 --> 15:17.090
Well, you didn't see mine!
Eddie's not at fault, Lou.

15:17.133 --> 15:19.570
Old lead-foot here came
screaming around that corner

15:19.614 --> 15:21.094
way too fast.

15:21.137 --> 15:22.747
You are
such a hypocrite.

15:22.791 --> 15:25.141
You immediately blame me
'cause I'm the Asian driver.

15:25.185 --> 15:28.101
That's not what I'm doing.
I just assumed because you...

15:28.144 --> 15:30.146
Are Asian?!
[ Scoffs ] Just own it.

15:30.190 --> 15:32.366
Everybody's a little bit racist.
Even you.

15:32.409 --> 15:33.889
First you joke about it,

15:33.933 --> 15:35.108
then you hate it,
then you play into it?

15:35.151 --> 15:36.326
Make up your mind!

15:36.370 --> 15:38.198
You weren't supposed to be
driving at all.

15:38.241 --> 15:40.026
Your car.
This isn't your car.

15:40.069 --> 15:41.636
I have
my learner's permit.

15:41.679 --> 15:43.377
Not anymore.
I'm taking it away.

15:43.420 --> 15:45.379
Driving is a privilege,
not a right.

15:45.422 --> 15:47.163
Forget this, I'm out!

15:49.122 --> 15:51.907
Brian:
So, I guess we swap info

15:51.951 --> 15:54.692
and let the claims adjusters
figure out who caused what?

15:54.736 --> 15:58.435
♪♪

16:00.263 --> 16:02.265
Oh, sorry,
I'll give you the room.

16:02.309 --> 16:04.006
Don't want to be
a stick-in-the-mud.

16:06.487 --> 16:08.358
Oh, and I was
thinking about it.

16:08.402 --> 16:11.013
How is a stick-in-the-mud
a bad thing anyway?

16:11.057 --> 16:12.797
If it's lying flat,
you can step on it

16:12.841 --> 16:14.060
to keep
your shoes clean and --

16:14.103 --> 16:15.844
You're doing it right now.

16:15.887 --> 16:18.064
You pick apart
every little detail.

16:18.107 --> 16:20.718
When someone's telling a story,
when they're watching TV --

16:20.762 --> 16:22.894
I thought people liked it
when I corrected them

16:22.938 --> 16:24.157
so they can learn.

16:24.200 --> 16:26.420
Not really.
Especially notGrandma.

16:26.463 --> 16:30.076
But if I were ever wrong,
I'd want someone to correct me.

16:30.119 --> 16:32.904
You're not like most people.
You're special that way.

16:32.948 --> 16:34.036
But Grandma's stories
are so...

16:34.080 --> 16:36.908
Nonsensical? Who cares?

16:36.952 --> 16:38.214
It's hard for me
to enjoy something

16:38.258 --> 16:40.260
when I know it's wrong.

16:40.303 --> 16:42.088
The little voice in my brain
won't quiet

16:42.131 --> 16:43.219
until I fix the mistake.

16:43.263 --> 16:45.265
That's Mom's voice.

16:45.308 --> 16:47.136
It's okay to turn it off
every now and then.

16:47.180 --> 16:49.095
Really?
We're allowed to do that?

16:50.574 --> 16:53.403
♪♪

16:53.447 --> 16:54.535
[ Gearshift clicks ]

16:54.578 --> 16:56.058
[ Chuckles ]

16:56.102 --> 16:57.842
Wish they stayed
that size forever.

16:57.886 --> 16:58.930
Yeah.

16:58.974 --> 17:00.671
Hey, thanks
for driving us around.

17:00.715 --> 17:03.152
And again, sorry.
I didn't know.

17:03.196 --> 17:05.763
It's okay.
He just doesn't get that.

17:05.807 --> 17:07.287
That you're only trying
to protect him.

17:07.330 --> 17:08.505
Exactly.
Yeah.

17:08.549 --> 17:10.942
Learning to drive is a huge
moment in a kid's life.

17:10.986 --> 17:13.075
I didn't want this thing
to overshadow it.

17:13.119 --> 17:15.860
I never thought I'd be the one
he first felt it from.

17:15.904 --> 17:17.862
Well, look at the bright side,
Lou, it's the '90s.

17:17.906 --> 17:19.342
People are getting hip.

17:19.386 --> 17:20.952
All this race stuff
is almost done with.

17:22.780 --> 17:25.261
Who knew teaching your kid to
drive could be so complicated?

17:25.305 --> 17:27.568
[ Laughs ] Yeah. It was
the same for me and Nicole.

17:27.611 --> 17:29.309
It's crazy for every parent.

17:29.352 --> 17:31.528
You know, it's a time
of very mixed emotions.

17:31.572 --> 17:33.791
Not only is it one
of the last bonding moments,

17:33.835 --> 17:37.012
but you're teaching them to
drive right out of the nest.

17:37.056 --> 17:38.666
I didn't even
think of that.

17:38.709 --> 17:42.235
Yeah. Maybe sandbagging your kid
wasn't just to protect him.

17:42.278 --> 17:44.367
Maybe part of it was
that you're just not ready

17:44.411 --> 17:46.456
to have him go out
and get mustard without you.

17:46.500 --> 17:48.719
[ Chuckles ]

18:07.303 --> 18:09.262
Hey.
[ Clears throat ]

18:09.305 --> 18:11.264
It has been
pointed out to me

18:11.307 --> 18:13.048
that I can be
a stick-in-the-mud.

18:15.964 --> 18:18.140
I tried to soften it.

18:18.184 --> 18:21.926
Well, either way, it is
a habit I am trying to fix.

18:21.970 --> 18:24.755
Until then, I figured
I'd fill my mouth with taffy

18:24.799 --> 18:28.019
as insurance should I feel
the urge to enlighten ignorance.

18:29.456 --> 18:31.240
Great.

18:31.284 --> 18:34.287
Then I will stick this giant
piece of candy in my mouth

18:34.330 --> 18:35.897
and try to have
a good time.

18:46.821 --> 18:48.170
[ Laughs ]

18:56.047 --> 18:58.398
[ Owl singing
operatically ]

18:58.441 --> 19:00.400
[ Chuckles ]

19:00.443 --> 19:02.271
I might need
some of that taffy.

19:03.272 --> 19:09.191
♪♪

19:09.235 --> 19:11.367
Hey, playing
some football?

19:17.286 --> 19:19.462
Look, Eddie, when I was
a kid in Taiwan...

19:19.506 --> 19:20.637
You drove a bus.

19:20.681 --> 19:22.335
Hear me out.

19:22.378 --> 19:24.337
Yes, I drove a bus.

19:24.380 --> 19:27.470
But I learned to drive it in a
place where everyone was Asian.

19:27.514 --> 19:28.602
Sounds chaotic.

19:28.645 --> 19:30.647
It was a little hectic,
yes,

19:30.691 --> 19:32.823
but only because there were
so many people on the road.

19:32.867 --> 19:34.564
Of course. Sure.

19:34.608 --> 19:36.349
I know
I exaggerate the story.

19:36.392 --> 19:38.655
I take after your grandma
in that way.

19:38.699 --> 19:41.354
But the truth is, I had fun
learning to drive.

19:41.397 --> 19:43.834
And then I came here
and it became less fun.

19:43.878 --> 19:46.402
So I learned to beat people
to the punch

19:46.446 --> 19:48.926
by joking about it myself.

19:48.970 --> 19:52.800
I don't know if making light
of it is good or bad or both.

19:52.843 --> 19:56.804
I just want things
to be easier for you.

19:56.847 --> 20:00.373
And I appreciate you clicking in
on this particular instance,

20:00.416 --> 20:03.071
but I deal with this nonsense
all the time.

20:03.114 --> 20:04.681
Do you know how many people
have asked me

20:04.725 --> 20:05.943
if I've seen "Rush Hour"?

20:05.987 --> 20:08.076
Me too!

20:08.119 --> 20:10.252
I guess you were
more ready than I knew.

20:10.296 --> 20:12.602
Dad, I'll be okay
out there.

20:12.646 --> 20:15.257
I promise.

20:15.301 --> 20:17.912
And I know you were just trying
to look out for me.

20:17.955 --> 20:19.609
Yeah.

20:19.653 --> 20:21.611
Also, maybe
I was a little over-cautious

20:21.655 --> 20:23.396
because I was having
a good time with you,

20:23.439 --> 20:25.354
and I didn't want it to end.

20:28.749 --> 20:30.968
Now, let's go grab the rest
of the family

20:31.012 --> 20:33.536
and go to this movie everyone
thinks we need to see.

20:33.580 --> 20:35.103
It looks good.

20:35.146 --> 20:37.410
I know.

20:37.453 --> 20:39.673
Hey, you know what?
I'm a little tired.

20:39.716 --> 20:41.152
Why don't you drive?

20:41.196 --> 20:42.850
Really?

20:42.893 --> 20:45.853
Oh, these are just
the old house keys.

20:45.896 --> 20:48.421
That was the final test.
You pass.

20:54.209 --> 20:55.515
Well, what did
everyone think of the movie?

20:55.558 --> 20:57.778
The black man who talked
like a girl was funny,

20:57.821 --> 20:59.780
but I thought there was
one too many cheap jokes

20:59.823 --> 21:01.912
at the expense
of Chinese stereotypes.

21:01.956 --> 21:04.480
Coming from the lady who brought
food from home to the mall.

21:04.524 --> 21:06.352
That's not a thing.
It's just smart.

21:06.395 --> 21:07.353
I'm just glad I got to see

21:07.396 --> 21:09.485
some Asian representation
on the big screen.

21:09.529 --> 21:11.922
Well, I was impressed
that a movie called "Rush Hour"

21:11.966 --> 21:14.098
never once made
a bad-Asian-driver joke.

21:14.142 --> 21:16.449
Maybe there's hope
for America yet.

21:20.540 --> 21:22.542
-Okay, chopsticks.
-Oh.

21:22.585 --> 21:26.197
♪♪
